clinical_study.brief_title: Safety and Tolerability Study of MDV3100 in Combination With Docetaxel in Men With Advanced Prostate Cancer
clinical_study.official_title: A PHASE 1B, OPEN-LABEL, SAFETY AND TOLERABILITY STUDY OF ORAL MDV3100 IN COMBINATION WITH DOCETAXEL IN MEN WITH ADVANCED PROSTATE CANCER

collaborator.agency: Medivation LLC, a wholly owned subsidiary of Pfizer Inc.

brief_summary.textblock: The purpose of this study is to determine the safety of MDV3100 given in combination with Docetaxel in men with advanced prostate cancer.

primary_outcome.measure: Percentage of Participants Who Required Study Drug Dose Reduction During Treatment Periods 1 and 2
primary_outcome.time_frame: Treatment Period 1 (Day 1) up to end of Treatment Period 2 (42 days)
primary_outcome.description: Percentage of participants that required dose reductions of Docetaxel and Enzalutamide treatment were reported in this outcome measure. Dose modifications (interruptions or dose reductions) were permitted for participants who had adverse events that were intolerable or could not be improved by other means. Dose reductions or delays were determined according to the prescribing information and at the discretion of the investigator.

primary_outcome.measure: Percentage of Participants Who Discontinued Study Drug Due to an Adverse Event (AE)
primary_outcome.time_frame: Treatment Period 1 (Day 1) up to end of study treatment (maximum 70 months)
primary_outcome.description: AE was any untoward medical occurrence in participant who received study drug without regard to possibility of causal relationship. Percentage of participants that discontinued study drug due to adverse events were reported in this outcome measure.

group.title: Docetaxel 75 mg/m^2+ Enzalutamide 160 mg
group.description: Docetaxel 75 milligrams per square meter (mg/m^2) was administered as intravenous (IV) infusion for 1 hour on Day 1 of each treatment period (each treatment period was of 21 days). From Day 2 of treatment period 1, participants received a single oral dose of Enzalutamide (MDV3100) 160 milligrams (mg) (4 capsules of 40 mg each) once daily. Participants received a single oral dose of Dexamethasone 8 mg prior to each Docetaxel infusion and Prednisone (5 mg) once daily on the days of Docetaxel administration then twice daily every day thereafter as long as Docetaxel treatment continued. Participants who tolerated treatment with Docetaxel and Enzalutamide continued to receive the combined therapy. Participants who discontinued Docetaxel were allowed to continue the treatment with Enzalutamide 160 mg once daily up to the end of study treatment (maximum of Month 70).

baseline.population: Intent-to-treat (ITT) population included all enrolled participants.
